I noticed an error in my application using  btConvexHullShape constructor with parameters. Perhaps I am mistaking, but it seems like constructor suggests that X, Y and Z coordinates are always int first positions of vertices data. That is not always true, for example you can have normals, uv before xyz values.

That is why i suggest to add an offset attribute to the constructor, like : 

```c++
    btConvexHullShape ::btConvexHullShape (const btScalar* points,int numPoints,int stride, int offset) :     btPolyhedralConvexAabbCachingShape ()
    {
     m_shapeType = CONVEX_HULL_SHAPE_PROXYTYPE;
     m_unscaledPoints.resize(numPoints);
   
    unsigned char* pointsAddress = (unsigned char*)points;
   
    for (int i=0;i<numPoints;i++)
    {
    btScalar* point = (btScalar*)pointsAddress;
    m_unscaledPoints[i] = btVector3(point[0 + offset], point[1 + offset], point[2 + offset]);
    pointsAddress += stride;
    }
   
    recalcLocalAabb();
   
    }
```

